<HEADLINE> Kenya Starts Sex Education in Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenya will launch sex
education program in primary and secondary schools and teacher
training colleges when schools reopen next Monday, with an initial
400 teachers trained for the exercise, local media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Ministry of Education said the program is a
product of joint efforts by local and international donors, anti-
HIV/AIDS groups and the government through the National AIDS
Control Council.
</P>
<P>
AIDS is widespread in the country, claiming 500 lives daily.
</P>
